HEADWORD: Taxicorn
<hw>Tax"i*corn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>taxus</ets> a yew + <ets>cornu</ets> a horn: cf. F.
<ets>taxicorne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a family of
beetles (<fam>Taxicornes</fam>) whose antennae are largest at the tip.
Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

